WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.000
narrator: exit nodes — letting one peer relay general internet traffic.

00:00:05.000 --> 00:00:15.000
narrator: tailscale up with --advertise-exit-node opts a host in.

00:00:15.000 --> 00:00:25.000
narrator: the operator approves the advertisement from headscale.

00:00:25.000 --> 00:00:35.000
narrator: another peer selects the exit with tailscale up --exit-node.

00:00:35.000 --> 00:00:45.000
narrator: curl ifconfig.me from the client returns the exit IP.

00:00:45.000 --> 00:00:55.000
narrator: bandwidth is now metered by the operator-side analytics.

00:00:55.000 --> 00:01:05.000
narrator: revoking the advertisement immediately drops traffic back.
